<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-1166] Applications using Log4j-2.5 with monitorInterval never shut down</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-1166</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The new WatchManager introduced in 2.5 uses a ScheduledThreadPoolExecutor so it can roll over triggered by a timer event instead of a log event.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The executor currently uses the standard thread factory, which creates non-daemon threads. This means that applications that use Log4j 2 and have &lt;tt&gt;monitorInterval=&quot;...&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; in their configuration will never shut down.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is to pass a &lt;tt&gt;DaemonThreadFactory&lt;/tt&gt; to the ScheduledThreadPoolExecutor constructor. (This also allows us to specify a better name than &quot;pool-1-thread-1&quot;.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
